The condition $\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{v} = \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}$ can be written as $\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 = \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}.$  Hence, the set of vectors $\mathbf{v}$ we seek consists of all vectors $\mathbf{v}$ that satisfy
\[\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 - \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} = 0.\]This equation defines a sphere, centered at the origin.  We can compute the radius of this sphere as follows:
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 - \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} &= 0 \\
\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 &= \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= 10v_1 - 40v_2 + 8v_3 \\
