The set of vectors $\mathbf{v}$ such that
\[\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{v} = \mathbf{v} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}\]is the set of vectors $\mathbf{v}$ that satisfy
\[\mathbf{v} \cdot (\mathbf{v} - \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}) = 0.\]This expands as $\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{v} - \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \mathbf{v} = 0,$ or
\[\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 - \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \mathbf{v} = 0.\]Then
\[\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 = \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \mathbf{v}.\]We can interpret this as the set of points that are equidistant from the origin and the plane through the origin with normal vector $\begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}.$

