The distance between the origin and the plane with normal vector $\mathbf{n}$ and containing the point $\mathbf{p}$ is given by
\[\frac{|\mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{n}|}{\|\mathbf{n}\|}.\]Hence, the distance between the origin and the plane we are interested in is
\[\frac{|\begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \mathbf{v}|}{\|\begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}\|} = \frac{|10v_1 - 40v_2 + 8v_3|}{\sqrt{1740}}.\]Thus, the volume of the solid is
\[\frac{4}{3} \pi \left( \frac{|10v_1 - 40v_2 + 8v_3|}{\sqrt{1740}} \right)^3.\]We can compute that
\[10v_1 - 40v_2 + 8v_3 = (\mathbf{v} - \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1/2 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}) \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix}.\]Thus,
\[\left| 10v_1 - 40v_2 + 8v_3 \right| = \left| (\mathbf{v} - \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1/2 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}) \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 10 \\ -40 \\ 8 \end{pmatrix} \right| = |520 - 20v_1 + 20v_2 + 40v_3|.\]Therefore, the volume of the solid is
\[\frac{4}{3} \pi \cdot \frac{1}{1740} \cdot |520 - 20v_1 + 20v_2 + 40v_3|^3.\]Since
\[520 - 20v_1 + 20v_2 + 40v_3 = 20(13 - v_1 + v_2 + 2v_3),\]the volume of the solid is
\[\frac{4}{3} \pi \cdot \frac{1}{1740} \cdot 8000 = \boxed{\frac{128}{87} \pi}.\]

